# Summary of project 

This project aims to develop a system which monitors ambient light with an LDR and turns on a main LED at dusk and off at dawn. It also turns it off during the hours of 1am to 5am to save energy. 
It stays synchronised with the sun by detecting dusk and dawn where it computes solar midnight as the midpoint of the night. The system also applies a correction to ensure the internal clock would 
not drift out of syncing with real time. To ensure efficiency, 24 hours was recalibrated into 24 seconds for rapid prototyping.



# Key Performance Criteria 
To determine the success of the system, the criteria below were established: 
- LED turns off between the hours of 1am to 5am (4 hours = 4 seconds in the LED)
- Displays the current hour of the day in the LED array 
- Adjusts for daylight savings time between the last Sunday in March and last Sunday in October. 
- Always in sync with the sun



